Sentencas: In this work, the electrical and electrochemical performances of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 (LNF) cathode contact and current collecting layer are investigated.
Titulo: Electrical and Electrochemical Performances Evaluation of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 Cathode Contact and Current Collecting Layer in SOFCs

Sentencas: The screen-printed LNF thin film on LSCF-GDC cathode effectively improves the performance of anode supported single cell with maximum power density increase by similar to 15% and polarization resistance decrement by similar to 24%.
Titulo: Electrical and Electrochemical Performances Evaluation of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 Cathode Contact and Current Collecting Layer in SOFCs

Sentencas: However, the LNF layer is found to hinder oxygen diffusion under low cathode oxygen partial pressure below similar to 0.07 atm.
Titulo: Electrical and Electrochemical Performances Evaluation of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 Cathode Contact and Current Collecting Layer in SOFCs

Sentencas: For the application as thick contact layer, an optimized method is developed in combination with alternate ink deposition and drying processes, to provide decent structural stability and interfacial contact.
Titulo: Electrical and Electrochemical Performances Evaluation of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 Cathode Contact and Current Collecting Layer in SOFCs

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) of thick LNF contact layer shows high long-term stability under current load of 300 mA cm(-2).
Titulo: Electrical and Electrochemical Performances Evaluation of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 Cathode Contact and Current Collecting Layer in SOFCs

Sentencas: The ASR stabilizes at 0.086 omega center dot cm(2) for more than 1600 h. Moreover, the LNF contact layer operates stably after 7 thermal cycles.
Titulo: Electrical and Electrochemical Performances Evaluation of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 Cathode Contact and Current Collecting Layer in SOFCs

Sentencas: The results indicate that, LNF is promisingly applicable as current contact and collecting material in solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Electrical and Electrochemical Performances Evaluation of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 Cathode Contact and Current Collecting Layer in SOFCs
